 * Log chef-solo output
 * Install gist & hub
 * Install tmux 2.0
 * Update git

## OSX

 * Install Apple Command Line Developer Tools
 * Turn on SSH
 * Auto-hide Dock
 * Set Dock size small
 * Remove things from Dock
 * Set Keyboard Key Repeat and Delay
 * Solarized Terminal Colors (https://github.com/tomislav/osx-terminal.app-colors-solarized)
 * Set shell to /usr/local/bin/zsh (set /etc/shells)
 * Set background to solid black
 * Chrome: Warn Before Quitting
 * Install berkshelf (sudo gem install berks)
 * Install Chrome Google Voice and Video plugin
 * https://gist.github.com/brandonb927/3195465

## Ubuntu Root SSH Agent Forwarding

If root doesn't have permission to the shared $SSH_AUTH_SOCK see
http://stackoverflow.com/a/26497532.

## Raspberry Pi Notes

> sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get upgrade -y
> sudo raspi-config

Add to ~/.profile:

```
node_path=(/usr/local/lib/nodejs/node-*/bin)
export PATH=$node_path:$PATH
```

> source ~/.profile

> mkdir projects
> cd projects/

> sudo apt-get install git

> git clone git@github.com:parshap/devbox.git
> cd devbox/

> ./linux-setup.sh

Switch users to parshap

Change shell to zsh

Copy ~/.profile changes to ~/.zshrc
